This was originally raised by the VS for Mac team as they were seeing the issue w/ their Angular project template.  The details of that issue and my analysis can be found in https://github.com/mono/mono/issues/15738.  

The gist of the issue is that the angular project type does npm install and then they traverse the node_modules directories recursively.  

```
static IEnumerable<T> ExpandWildcardFilePath<T> (....) {
   ....
   if (recursive) {
      // Recursive search. Try to match the remaining subpath in all subdirectories.
      foreach (var dir in Directory.EnumerateDirectories (basePath))
         res = res.Concat (ExpandWildcardFilePath (project, dir, baseRecursiveDir, true, filePath, func, directoryExcludeRegex));
   }
}
```

Now, the argument could be made not to recurse (or read through the enumerator first) and that would be reasonable.  However, I think there may be opportunities to improve our underlying handle usage / lifetime.

